      • subscriber

        public static <T> Flow.Subscriber<T> subscriber​(Function<T,Boolean> onNextFunction)
        Creates Flow.Subscriber that will delegate Flow.Subscriber.onNext(Object) to specified onNextFunction function.

        Created subscriber automatically requests all events in it's Flow.Subscriber.onSubscribe(Flow.Subscription) method.

        Function onNextFunction returns false in case user wants to cancel current subscription.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the subscribed item type
        Parameters:
        onNextFunction - onNext functionality
        Returns:
        Subscriber implementation that delegates it's onNext to specified onNextFunction

      • suspendablePublisher

        public static <T> Flow.Publisher<T> suspendablePublisher​(Flow.Publisher<T> delegatePublisher,
                                                         Runnable onFirstSubscriptionRequest,
                                                         Runnable onLastSubscriptionCancel)
        Creates a wrapper of specified Flow.Publisher that supports "active" and "suspended" states.

        Publisher starts in "suspended" state. With first subscriber request it switches into "active" state. A onFirstSubscriptionRequest runnable is executed. With last subscriber cancel it switches back into "suspended" state. A onLastSubscriptionCancel runnable is executed.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the published item type
        Parameters:
        delegatePublisher - publisher used to delegate to
        onFirstSubscriptionRequest - hook invoked in case the first subscriber has requested the publisher.
        onLastSubscriptionCancel - hook invoked in case the last subscriber has canceled it's subscription.
        Returns:
        new instance of suspendable Flow.Publisher.

        Returns:
